<head>WEEK</head>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">星期</item>
        <item xml:lang="och">旬</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>PERIOD of TYPICALLY 7 OR 10 DAYS into which the MONTH is DIVIDED.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The general term for the ten-day week, or decameron, was xún 旬 which is already current on OBI, being an important dimension of the organisation of Shāng dynasty state rituals.</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>星期</p>
